    "content": "<html>\n<head>\n    <title>Hash Functions</title>\n    <style>\n        body {\n            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\n        }\n    </style>\n</head>\n<body>\n    <h1>Hash Functions</h1>\n    <p>Hash functions are one-way functions that take input data and produce a fixed-size string of characters, known as a hash value or digest.</p>\n    <p>Here's an example of a simple hash function in JavaScript, using the SHA-256 algorithm.</p>\n    <script>\n        function hashFunction(inputData) {\n            const hash = crypto.createHash('sha256');\n            hash.update(inputData);\n            return hash.digest('hex');\n        }\n\n        const inputData = \"Hello, World!\";\n        const hashValue = hashFunction(inputData);\n        console.log(`Hash value for ${inputData}: ${hashValue}`);\n\n        // Let's try a different hash function, MD5\n        const md5Hash = crypto.createHash('md5');\n        md5Hash.update(inputData);\n        const md5HashValue = md5Hash.digest('hex');\n        console.log(`MD5 hash value for ${inputData}: ${md5HashValue}`);\n    </script>\n</body>\n</html>"
